The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Government nod for big match dates
 BY A STAFF REPORTER Calcutta: The IFA has formally requested state sports minister Subhas Chakraborty to grant permission to host the National Football League (NFL) matches between East Bengal and Mohammedan Sporting on January 16 and East Bengal versus Mohun Bagan on January 22. The IFA authorities informed on Friday that Chakraborty had promised them to see enough police cover be there to help the matches take place on proposed dates. Earlier, it was decided that East Bengal would take on Mohun Bagan on January 21 and Mohammedan Sporting a couple of days later.  Douglas return East Bengal are hoping Douglas da Silva will be back for their NFL match against Mohun Bagan on January 22. According to a senior club official, Douglas is recovering well from the leg injury and should be available for the crunch tie. However, captain Suley Musah has been ruled out of the meets first leg. In fact, it may take him more time to recover if Musah doesnt undergo the operation for the ligament tear.  Copyright 
